<item>
            <title>[SOLR-5675] cloud-scripts/zkcli.bat: quote option  -Dlog4j...</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5675</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In Skript zkcli.bat this java command line is build:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;%JVM%&quot; -Dlog4j.configuration=&lt;a href=&quot;file:%SDIR%log4j.properties&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;file:%SDIR%\log4j.properties&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The command failes if %SDIR% contains spaces (&quot;C:\Program Files\...&quot;).&lt;br/&gt;
Quoting the hole option &quot;-Dlog4j.configuration=&lt;a href=&quot;file:%SDIR%log4j.properties&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;file:%SDIR%\log4j.properties&lt;/a&gt;&quot; solved the isssue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows 7 64 bit&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
